  "readme": "# postcss-selector-not [![Build Status](https://travis-ci.org/postcss/postcss-selector-not.svg?branch=master)](https://travis-ci.org/postcss/postcss-selector-not)\r\n\r\n> PostCSS plugin to transform `:not()` W3C CSS leve 4 pseudo class to :not() CSS level 3 selectors\r\n\r\nhttp://dev.w3.org/csswg/selectors-4/#negation\r\n\r\n## Installation\r\n\r\n```console\r\n$ npm install postcss-selector-not\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Usage\r\n\r\n```js\r\nvar postcss = require(\"postcss\")\r\n\r\nvar output = postcss()\r\n  .use(require(\"postcss-selector-not\"))\r\n  .process(require(\"fs\").readFileSync(\"input.css\", \"utf8\"))\r\n  .css\r\n```\r\n\r\nUsing this `input.css`:\r\n\r\n```css\r\np:not(:first-child, .special) {\r\n  color: red;\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nyou will get:\r\n\r\n```css\r\np:not(:first-child), p:not(.special) {\r\n  color: red;\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## [Changelog](CHANGELOG.md)\r\n\r\n## [License](LICENSE)\r\n",
